name: Dark Well
description:
Dark Well

The forest grows dark
the leaves of all the stories written by the sun
torn away, weightless and wiped clean 
of any wrong, floating forgiven
into the open arms
of the deep dark pool between my breasts
that welcomes you to dive into the stars
where our roots make love in a tangle of snakes
where our knots uncoil into snaky rivers
two snaky rivers into a sea
a sea where there is neither you nor me.
